<!-- REQUIRED -->
## Research Freshness Policy
<!-- ADAPT: Explain when model memory is not enough and current evidence is required. -->
- Use current primary sources for external APIs, framework versions, deployment standards, and security-sensitive implementation details.
- Prefer official documentation, specifications, or authoritative release notes over memory or third-party summaries.
- Record what was checked and when in `docs/research/RESEARCH-REGISTRY.md`.
- If current evidence is missing for a high-impact choice, pause and resolve that gap before implementation proceeds.

<!-- REQUIRED -->
## Deviation Policy
<!-- ADAPT: How deliberate trade-offs are handled. -->
- Every intentional compromise must be logged in `docs/decisions/DEVIATIONS.md`.
- Each deviation should state the reason, impact, owner, and review date.
- Temporary shortcuts must not silently become permanent defaults.
